wdi-DT.DOD.DECT.CD.def: Total external debt is debt owed to nonresidents repayable in currency, goods, or services. It is the sum of public, publicly guaranteed, and private nonguaranteed long-term debt, short-term debt, and use of IMF credit. Data are in current U.S. dollars.
wdi-DT.DOD.DECT.CD.name: External debt stocks
